<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>CoLab LTI Registration</title>
  <style>
    body { font-family: sans-serif; max-width: 600px; margin: 60px auto; padding: 0 20px; color: #333; }
    .success { border-left: 4px solid #4caf50; padding: 12px 16px; background: #f1f8f1; }
    .error   { border-left: 4px solid #f44336; padding: 12px 16px; background: #fdf1f1; }
    .detail  { margin-top: 16px; font-size: 0.9em; color: #555; }
    code     { background: #eee; padding: 2px 5px; border-radius: 3px; }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <h2>CoLab &mdash; LTI Dynamic Registration</h2>

  <% if @registration_error.present? %>
    <div class="error">
      <strong>Registration error:</strong> <%= @registration_error %>
    </div>
    <p class="detail">
      Check that the CoLab dev server is running (<code>dev_serv.sh -t</code>)
      and that Moodle can reach <code>https://app:3443</code> over the Docker network.
    </p>
  <% elsif @client_id.present? %>
    <div class="success">
      <strong>Registration complete.</strong>
      CoLab has been registered as an LTI&nbsp;1.3 tool in Moodle.
    </div>
    <p class="detail">
      <% if @platform_issuer.present? %>
        Platform: <code><%= @platform_issuer %></code><br>
      <% end %>
      Client ID: <code><%= @client_id %></code><br>
      You can close this tab and return to Moodle.
    </p>
  <% else %>
    <div class="success">
      <strong>Tool configuration returned.</strong>
      CoLab responded to the Dynamic Registration request.
      <% if @platform_issuer.blank? %>
        No <code>openid_configuration</code> URL was provided, so no
        server-to-server registration was performed &mdash; this is expected
        when fetching the configuration document directly.
      <% else %>
        The platform at <code><%= @platform_issuer %></code> did not supply a
        <code>registration_endpoint</code>; the tool configuration was not
        automatically saved.  Use the platform details printed by
        <code>bin/setup_moodle_course</code> to add a deployment manually in
        CoLab&rsquo;s LTI Deployments admin page.
      <% end %>
    </div>
  <% end %>
</body>
</html>
